The goal is to prove `HasLorentzType T p 1 p ∞ μ ν (4 * c / p)`.
The definition of `HasLorentzType T p q r s μ ν C` is:
`∀ f hf, eLpNorm (T f) q (ν.restrict G) ≤ C * eLorentzNorm f p q μ * (ν G) ^ r⁻¹.toReal`
for all measurable sets G with finite measure.

We need to show:
`∀ f hf, eLpNorm (T f) 1 (ν.restrict G) ≤ (4 * c / p) * eLorentzNorm f p 1 μ * (ν G) ^ p'⁻¹.toReal`

The proof strategy is to use the fact that any complex function `f` can be decomposed into four non-negative real functions:
`f = 1 • Re(f) - 1 • Re(f) + I • Im(f) - I • Im(f)`
This decomposition is similar to writing `f = a + bi` where `a, b` are real functions, and then considering the four components: `a, -a, b, -b`.

The decomposition used in the code is:
`g = (1 : 𝕂) • (algebraMap ℝ 𝕂 ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ g₁) + (-1 : 𝕂) • (algebraMap ℝ 𝕂 ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ g₂) + (RCLike.I : 𝕂) • (algebraMap ℝ 𝕂 ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ g₃) + (-RCLike.I : 𝕂) • (algebraMap ℝ 𝕂 ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ g₄)`
where `g₁ = fun x ↦ Real.toNNReal (RCLike.re (g x))`, `g₂ = fun x ↦ Real.toNNReal (- RCLike.re (g x))`, `g₃ = fun x ↦ Real.toNNReal (RCLike.im (g x))`, `g₄ = fun x ↦ Real.toNNReal (- RCLike.im (g x))`.

